 Attracting global capital to drive Nigeria’s economic reforms as well as sustainable growth is the latest objective of the Nigerian Stock Exchange in partnership with its London Stock Exchange. CNBC Africa’s Christy Cole caught up with the CEO of the NSE Oscar Onyema and Gokul Mani, Head Primary Markets, Middle East, Africa and Asia of the London Stock Exchange to discuss this on the side-lines of the dual listing event in Lagos. https://www.cnbcafrica.com/videos/